1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Not long ago in Poland,
there lived a man

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
named Kornel Morawiecki.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,000
He loved science,
freedom,
and mysteries.

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:20,000
By day, he taught students
how the world works.

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:25,000
After hours,
he did very brave things.

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Did you know
some books and newspapers

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:35,000
were banned back then?

8
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Kornel helped print them
in secret.

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:45,000
So people could learn
the truth.

10
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:50,000
The most special place
in his life

11
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:55,000
was a house nearby
called Kornelówka.

12
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:00,000
It was not
a normal house.

13
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Kornel built it himself

14
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:10,000
from wooden railway ties.

15
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:15,000
It stood among trees,
like an adventure hut.

16
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:20,000
To buy the land,
he became… a farmer!

17
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:25,000
He learned to farm
and passed an exam,

18
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:30,000
even though he was
a scientist at heart.

19
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Guests often came,
saying they picked mushrooms.

20
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:40,000
But they came
for something else.

21
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:45,000
Secret meetings happened here,
for a free Poland.

22
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Kornel founded
Fighting Solidarity.

23
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:55,000
In autumn 1990,
the house burned down.

24
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:01,000
But his son rebuilt it.
Freedom lives there again.